---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Patterns"
  description="Complete UI patterns for building with Vanilla Breeze. Ready-to-use navigation, forms, marketing sections, and application layouts."
  currentSection="examples"
>
  <h1>Patterns</h1>
  <p class="lead">Complete UI patterns built with semantic HTML and Vanilla Breeze. Each pattern demonstrates best practices for accessibility, progressive enhancement, and responsive design.</p>

  <layout-text>
    <p>Patterns are complete UI compositions that combine multiple Vanilla Breeze elements. Unlike snippets (isolated building blocks), patterns show how elements work together in real-world layouts. Copy the HTML directly or use them as reference for your own implementations.</p>
  </layout-text>

  <section>
    <h2>Navigation</h2>
    <p>Navigation patterns for headers, sidebars, breadcrumbs, and pagination.</p>
    <layout-grid data-min="250px" data-gap="m">
      <a href="/docs/patterns/navigation/navbar/" class="section-card">
        <h3>Navbar</h3>
        <p>Header navigation with dropdowns, search, and mobile menu.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/patterns/navigation/breadcrumb/" class="section-card">
        <h3>Breadcrumb</h3>
        <p>Hierarchical navigation showing the current location.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/docs/patterns/navigation/pagination/" class="section-card">
        <h3>Pagination</h3>
